  "novel_contributions": [
    "We propose a new architecture (MBT) for audiovisual fusion.",
    "We restrict the flow of cross-modal information between latent units through tight fusion ‘bottlenecks’.",
    "We apply MBT to image and spectrogram patches and explore ablations related to the fusion layer, the sampling of inputs and data size.",
    "We set the new state-of-the-art for video classification across a number of popular audio-visual benchmarks, including AudioSet, Epic-Kitchens100 and VGGSound."
  ],
  "key_claims": [
    {
      "claim": "MBT introduces fusion bottlenecks that force cross-modal information to pass through a small number of latent units, reducing quadratic attention cost while improving or matching performance.",
